DATA CLOUD
Requesting Data Deletion or Right to Be Forgotten

Learn more about how to submit Data Deletion requests in Data Cloud.

You can submit Data Deletion requests of individual data profiles in Data Cloud. All requests must be submitted using the Consent API.

A Data Deletion request deletes the specified individual record from the Individual DMO and the related DMOs.

WARNING Data must be related to the Individual DMO for it to be included in the deletion. Data stored in unrelated DMOs won’t be deleted.

Data Deletion requests are reprocessed at 30, 60, and 90 days to ensure a full deletion. You must submit any data deletion requests in all connected systems and Salesforce clouds.

EXAMPLE

The example below shows the deletion behavior among many DLOs, wherein only specific ones are impacted by the deletion request. For instance, matching records from DLO 2 are deleted because it’s mapped directly to the Individual DMO, and matching records from DLO 4 and DLO 7 are deleted because they’re mapped to the Contact Point Address DMO. Matching records from the other DLOs aren’t deleted because they’re not mapped to either the Individual DMO or the Contact Point Address DMO.
